title: Plant scraps are the key ingredient in cheap, sustainable jet fuel

title_detail.value: Plant scraps are the key ingredient in cheap, sustainable jet fuel

summary: Scientists have developed a process for converting plant waste from agriculture and timber harvesting into high-density aviation fuel. Their research may help reduce CO2 emissions from airplanes and rockets.
